  └──────────────────────────────────────────┘

  Package Layout
  ──────────────
  com.edutrack.e_journal
  ├── config/        SecurityConfig, OpenApiConfig
  ├── controller/    One controller per domain
  ├── dto/           Request / response objects (Lombok)
  ├── entity/        JPA entities (Lombok @Data / @Builder)
  ├── repository/    Spring Data JPA interfaces
  ├── security/      JWT utilities, filters, UserDetailsService
  └── service/       Business logic


================================================================================
  3. JWT AUTHENTICATION FLOW
================================================================================

  LOGIN
  ─────
  Client                              Backend
    │                                   │
    │  POST /auth/login                 │
    │  { email, password }              │
    │──────────────────────────────────▶│
    │                                   │  AuthenticationManager.authenticate()
    │                                   │  BCrypt password check
    │                                   │  generateAccessToken()   24 h
    │                                   │  generateRefreshToken()   7 days
    │                                   │  Set-Cookie: refreshToken
    │                                   │              (HttpOnly, path=/auth)
    │◀──────────────────────────────────│
    │  { accessToken: "eyJ…" }          │


  AUTHENTICATED REQUEST
  ─────────────────────
  Client                              Backend
    │                                   │
    │  GET /api/profile                 │
    │  Authorization: Bearer eyJ…       │
    │──────────────────────────────────▶│
    │                                   │  JwtAuthenticationFilter:
    │                                   │    1. Extract Authorization header
    │                                   │    2. validateToken()  (sig + expiry)
    │                                   │    3. getEmailFromToken()
    │                                   │    4. CustomUserDetailsService
    │                                   │         .loadUserByUsername(email)
    │                                   │    5. Set SecurityContext
    │                                   │  @PreAuthorize role check
    │◀──────────────────────────────────│
    │  200 { profile data }             │


  TOKEN REFRESH
  ─────────────
  Client                              Backend
    │                                   │
    │  POST /auth/refresh               │
    │  Cookie: refreshToken=eyJ…        │
    │──────────────────────────────────▶│
    │                                   │  Read cookie → validate
    │                                   │  Extract email → load user
    │                                   │  generateAccessToken()
    │◀──────────────────────────────────│
    │  { accessToken: "eyJ…" }          │


  ACCESS TOKEN CLAIMS
  ───────────────────
  Claim    Value
  ─────    ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  sub      User's email address
  id       User's database primary key (Long)
  email    User's email address
  role     ADMIN | HEADMASTER | TEACHER | STUDENT | PARENT
  name     firstName + " " + lastName
  iat      Issued-at (epoch seconds)
  exp      iat + jwtExpirationInMs  (default 86400000 ms = 24 h)

  Refresh token contains only: sub, iat, exp (7 days).

  FRONTEND TOKEN HANDLING
  ───────────────────────
  • Access token is stored in localStorage.
  • An Axios request interceptor attaches it as "Authorization: Bearer …"
    to every outgoing API call.
  • On a 401 response, the interceptor calls POST /auth/refresh using the
    HttpOnly cookie, updates the stored token, and retries the original request.
  • On logout or refresh failure, localStorage is cleared and the user is
    redirected to /login.


================================================================================
  4. SECURITY CONFIGURATION
================================================================================

  FILTER CHAIN ORDER
  ──────────────────
  1. RequestLoggingFilter
     Logs every request: method, path, status, duration, IP → requests.log

  2. LocalhostAdminFilter  (development only)
     When app.security.allow-localhost=true, any request from 127.0.0.1 / ::1
     that has no Authorization header is automatically authenticated with all
     five roles. MUST be set to false in production.

  3. JwtAuthenticationFilter
     Validates Bearer token, populates SecurityContext.

  PUBLIC ENDPOINTS (no token required)
  ─────────────────────────────────────
  POST  /auth/login
  POST  /auth/refresh
  POST  /auth/logout
  GET   /swagger-ui/**
  GET   /swagger-ui.html
  GET   /v3/api-docs/**

  All other paths require a valid JWT.

  CORS
  ────
  Allowed origin:   http://localhost:5173  (Vite dev server)
  Allowed methods:  GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, OPTIONS
  Credentials:      enabled  (required for the refresh-token cookie)

  For production: update corsConfigurationSource() in SecurityConfig
  to allow the real frontend domain.


================================================================================
  5. ROLE SYSTEM
================================================================================

  Role          Description
  ────────────  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  ADMIN         Global superuser. Full access to all schools and all data.
  HEADMASTER    Manages one school. Hires/fires staff, configures terms.
  TEACHER       Records grades, absences, complaints for assigned classes.
  STUDENT       Read-only access to own grades, absences, and complaints.
  PARENT        Read-only access to their child's grades, absences, complaints.

  Role is enforced at two levels:
    • Method-level  — @PreAuthorize on controller methods.
    • Service-level — ownership checks (e.g. a HEADMASTER may only modify
                      their own school; a TEACHER may only add grades to
                      classes assigned to them).


