================================================================================
  7. FRONTEND ROUTING
================================================================================

  AUTHENTICATION & REDIRECT
  ─────────────────────────
  On app load, AuthProvider decodes the stored access token from localStorage
  and populates the auth context (id, email, role, name).

  Every protected route is wrapped in ProtectedRoute, which:
    • Redirects to /login if the user is not authenticated.
    • Redirects to /unauthorized if the user's role is not in the allowed list.

  The root path "/" renders RoleRedirect, which sends the user to:
    ADMIN       →  /admin
    HEADMASTER  →  /headmaster
    TEACHER     →  /teacher
    STUDENT     →  /student
    PARENT      →  /parent


  PUBLIC ROUTES
  ─────────────
  /login          Login page
  /unauthorized   Access-denied page


  PROFILE  (all authenticated roles)
  ───────
  /profile


  ADMIN ROUTES
  ────────────
  /admin                  AdminHome
  /admin/manageUsers      User management
  /admin/viewSchools      School list
  /admin/viewSubjects     Subject list  (also HEADMASTER)


  HEADMASTER ROUTES
  ─────────────────
  /headmaster                HeadmasterHome
  /headmaster/mySchool       Manage own school
  /headmaster/viewParents    Parents at school
  /headmaster/viewStudents   Students at school
  /headmaster/viewTeachers   Teachers at school


  TEACHER ROUTES
  ──────────────
  /teacher                              TeacherHome
  /teacher/school                       View school info
  /teacher/teacherSchedule/:teacherId   Own schedule


  STUDENT / PARENT ROUTES
  ───────────────────────
  /student    StudentHome
  /parent     ParentHome


  SHARED — SCHEDULE
  ─────────────────
  /schedule/:classId     ADMIN, HEADMASTER, TEACHER, PARENT, STUDENT


  SHARED — GRADES
  ───────────────
  /grades                          ADMIN
  /grades/school/:schoolId         ADMIN, HEADMASTER
  /grades/class/:classId           ADMIN, HEADMASTER, TEACHER
  /grades/student/:studentId       ADMIN, HEADMASTER, TEACHER, PARENT, STUDENT
  /grades/me                       STUDENT


  SHARED — ABSENCES
  ─────────────────
  /absences                        ADMIN
  /absences/school/:schoolId       ADMIN, HEADMASTER
  /absences/class/:classId         ADMIN, HEADMASTER, TEACHER
  /absences/student/:studentId     ADMIN, HEADMASTER, TEACHER, PARENT, STUDENT
  /absences/me                     STUDENT


  SHARED — COMPLAINTS
  ───────────────────
  /complaints                      ADMIN
  /complaints/school/:schoolId     ADMIN, HEADMASTER
  /complaints/class/:classId       ADMIN, HEADMASTER, TEACHER
  /complaints/student/:studentId   ADMIN, HEADMASTER, TEACHER, PARENT, STUDENT


  STATISTICS
  ──────────
  /statistics/school/:schoolId     ADMIN, HEADMASTER
  /statistics/subject/:subjectId   ADMIN, HEADMASTER
  /statistics/teacher/:teacherId   ADMIN, HEADMASTER


  SELECTION HELPERS (picker pages)
  ────────────────────────────────
  /select/school/statistics        ADMIN
  /select/teacher/statistics       ADMIN, HEADMASTER
  /select/subject/statistics       ADMIN, HEADMASTER
  /select/class/schedule           ADMIN, HEADMASTER
  /select/class/grades             ADMIN, HEADMASTER, TEACHER
  /select/class/absences           ADMIN, HEADMASTER, TEACHER
  /select/class/complaints         ADMIN, TEACHER


================================================================================
  8. REQUEST LIFECYCLE  (end-to-end example)
================================================================================

  Scenario: a teacher submits a grade.

  1. Teacher clicks "Add grade" in ClassGrades.jsx.

  2. React sends:
       POST /api/grades
       Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1…
       Content-Type: application/json
       { studentId: 42, scheduleId: 7, value: 5.5 }

  3. RequestLoggingFilter: begins timing the request.

  4. LocalhostAdminFilter: Authorization header present → skip bypass.

  5. JwtAuthenticationFilter:
       a. Extracts token from "Authorization: Bearer …"
       b. JwtUtils.validateToken() — checks HMAC signature + expiry → OK
       c. JwtUtils.getEmailFromToken() → "teacher@school.bg"
       d. CustomUserDetailsService.loadUserByUsername("teacher@school.bg")
          → loads User from DB, wraps in UserDetails with role TEACHER
       e. Sets SecurityContext with UsernamePasswordAuthenticationToken

  6. Spring Security evaluates @PreAuthorize on GradeController.addGrade():
       hasRole('TEACHER') or hasRole('ADMIN') or hasRole('HEADMASTER') → PASS

  7. GradeController.addGrade() delegates to GradeService.addGrade():
       • Validates schedule entry exists
       • Validates student exists
       • Validates value is in {2, 2.5, 3, 3.5, 4, 4.5, 5, 5.5, 6}
       • Saves new Grade entity via GradeRepository

  8. Response:
       201 Created
       { id, studentId, subjectId, value, term, date, … }

  9. RequestLoggingFilter writes to requests.log:
       POST /api/grades → 201  (12 ms)  [127.0.0.1]

  10. React appends the new grade chip to the table without a page reload.


================================================================================
  9. CONFIGURATION REFERENCE
================================================================================

  File: backend/e-journal/src/main/resources/application.properties

  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ spring.application.name=e-journal                                       │
  │                                                                         │
  │ # Database                                                              │
  │ spring.datasource.url=jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5432/ejournal         │
  │ spring.datasource.username=ejournal_usr                                 │
  │ spring.datasource.password=ejournal_pwd                                 │
  │ spring.datasource.driver-class-name=org.postgresql.Driver              │
  │                                                                         │
  │ # JPA / Hibernate                                                       │
  │ spring.jpa.database-platform=org.hibernate.dialect.PostgreSQLDialect   │
  │ spring.jpa.show-sql=false                                               │
  │ spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=update                                    │
  │ spring.jpa.open-in-view=true                                            │
  │                                                                         │
  │ # JWT                                                                   │
  │ app.jwtSecret=<at-least-64-char-secret>                                 │
  │ app.jwtExpirationInMs=86400000      # 24 h (access token)              │
  │                                     # refresh token is always 7 days   │
  │                                                                         │
  │ # Security                                                              │
  │ app.security.allow-localhost=true   # false in production!             │
  │                                                                         │
  │ # Logging                                                               │
  │ app.logging.path=logs                                                   │
  │ logging.config=classpath:logback-spring.xml                             │
  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  LOG FILES  (written to app.logging.path directory)
  ─────────
  e-journal.log   Full application log (INFO+), rotated daily, 30-day retention
  requests.log    One line per HTTP request: method · path · status · ms · IP
                  Rotated daily, 14-day retention.

  PRODUCTION CHECKLIST
  ────────────────────
  □  Set app.security.allow-localhost=false
  □  Use a random JWT secret of at least 64 characters
  □  Update CORS allowed origins in SecurityConfig to the real domain
  □  Set spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=validate  (not update or create)
  □  Run as a dedicated low-privilege system user
     (see configure-debian.sh for the systemd service setup)
  □  Serve the React build (frontend/dist/) via nginx or similar reverse proxy
  □  Point the Vite proxy (or nginx) to backend :8080


